Sentencas: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells were heated from room temperature to an operating temperature of 450 degrees C.
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering

Sentencas: The start-up heating rate was controlled at three levels (10 K min(-1), 30 K min(-1), and 50 K min(-1)).
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering

Sentencas: For as-fabricated single cells, greater grain growth of the yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte and cathode platinum cluster growth were observed with an increasing start-up heating rate.
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering

Sentencas: As a result, the faradaic areaspecific resistance (ASR) significantly increased, and the performance of the cell decreased due to the sluggish oxygen reduction reaction originating from the loss of the reaction sites.
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering

Sentencas: However, after preannealing the single cells at 400 degrees C for 2 h prior to start-up, the change in grain size and faradaic ASR varied with the start-up heating rate was well suppressed by the enhanced interfacial stability between the electrolyte and cathode.
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering

Sentencas: The single cell samples for the experiments are composed of Pt-YSZ-Pt thin films supported on nanoporous anodic aluminum oxides.
Titulo: Influence of the start-up rate on the electrochemical impedance of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by reactive sputtering
